ent access.\n- The NoFly annotation on public interface classes ensures they don\u2019t override standard behavior.\n- Exception handling is managed to prevent null pointer exceptions when accessing collection properties.\n\nThis approach effectively refactored an internal class, dynamically gathering methods and ensuring flexibility without domain-specific knowledge, leveraging design patterns like generic reflection and dependency injection."}], "metadata": {"source": "ollama-deepseek-r1", "loser_idx": 9, "friend_idx": 9, "strategy": "with adversarial or trick elements", "tokens": 1188, "ts": "2026-01-23T01:24:31.238024"}}
