        report?.getStatus();\n        \n         // Let the exception propagate, unless it's possible to \n        // extract response status code as an error or success message.\n        if (report == null)\n            report = new RuntimeException();\n    }\n} else\n}\n// When I make a request that returns 429 for large responses.\n\nWait perhaps better to approach with:\n\npublic static void main(String[] args) {\n\n    org.apache HttpClient-one\n        .org.url\n        .url(\"https://example.com\")\n        .url(RequestMethod START))? { // unmodified request:\n      report();\n    }\n    try {\n        Send a GET request for 429 example: \"request is wrong size\"\n\n        (Response) response = client.send().headers().get(\"Content-Disposition\");\n        if (response == null)\n            ?? 1\n\nFinally, to handle all possibilities:\n\n} catch (Exception e) { }\n```\n\nWait this is getting messy. Let me think of a better way.\n\nSo the structure would be like: \n\n- Have each code in a separate test case or try block.\n- For non-success codes (e.g., 304), check that response has null status.\n\nThus:\n\npublic static void main(String[] args) {\n\n    // Setup the HTTP client\n\n    org.apache HttpClient-one\n        .org.url\n        .url(\"https://example.com\")\n        .url(RequestMethod START))? {}\n        report();\n} else {\n    try {\n        String[] statusCodesToTest = { \"200 OK\", \"304 Not Modified\", \n            \"401 Unauthorized\", \"415 Conflict\", \"429 Large Response\", \"422 Smooth Replay\" };\n        for (int i=0; i < statusCodesToTest.length; i++) {\n            String status = statusCodesToTest[i];\n            report();\n\n            org.apache HttpConferences.StatusStatusCode expectedStatus = \n                new org.apache HttpClient-fourier.StatusCode(status);\n            try {\n                sendRequest(expectedStatus);\n\n                if (status is 415 then expect to get some error message)\n\nBut without showing what can fail, let\u2019s proceed.\n\n**Example:**\n\n1. **Test for OK OK responses that should be successful.**\n   This sends a simple GET request and checks the status code.\n   \n2. **Test for Not Modified response:** Sends a PUT request back with nothing changed.\n   \n3. **Test for Unauthorized (401):** sends an API"}], "metadata": {"source": "ollama-deepseek-r1", "loser_idx": 14, "friend_idx": 1, "strategy": "comparing multiple valid approaches", "tokens": 2088, "ts": "2026-01-23T01:45:50.345737"}}
